The paper deals with coding theory, specifically cyclic codes and constacyclic codes over finite rings. This falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also involves algebraic structures and combinatorial designs, which could potentially place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or combinatorics (cs.CC) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the Gray map, which is a tool used in signal processing and communications (cs.SD).
